# =============================================================================
# TAConnect Frontend Environment Variables
# =============================================================================

# API URL (optional - defaults to relative path in production)
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# =============================================================================
# App URL (for SEO meta tags and social sharing)
# =============================================================================
# Set this to your domain when self-hosting.
# This URL is used for:
# - Canonical URLs for SEO
# - Open Graph meta tags (Facebook, LinkedIn sharing)
# - Twitter Card meta tags
# - Sitemap URLs
# - JSON-LD structured data
#
# Default: https://taconnect.netlify.app (official deployment)
# Examples:
#   - https://ta.youruniversity.edu
#   - https://taconnect.yourdomain.com
#   - http://localhost:3000 (for development)
VITE_APP_URL=https://taconnect.netlify.app

# =============================================================================
# Google Search Console Verification (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# Add your Google Search Console verification code for SEO indexing.
# Get your code from: https://search.google.com/search-console
# Only the code is needed (not the full meta tag).
#
# Example: If Google gives you:
#   <meta name="google-site-verification" content="ABC123XYZ" />
# Then set:
#   VITE_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=ABC123XYZ
#
# Leave empty or remove if you don't need Google Search Console verification.
# VITE_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=your-verification-code

# =============================================================================
# Push Notifications (Web Push API)
# =============================================================================
# VAPID (Voluntary Application Server Identification) public key for push notifications.
# This must match the VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY in the backend .env file.
#
# To generate VAPID keys:
# 1. Install web-push globally: npm install -g web-push
# 2. Generate keys: web-push generate-vapid-keys
# 3. Copy the public key here and the private key to backend .env
#
# Or generate using Python (in backend):
# pip install py-vapid
# vapid --gen
#
# The key below is a placeholder - generate your own for production!
